text: The Swiss franc (, French and Romansh: franc, ; sign: Fr. or SFr.; code: CHF) is the currency of Switzerland and Liechtenstein. The smaller denomination, a hundredth of a franc, is a Rappen (Rp.) in German, centime (c.) in French, centesimo (ct.) in Italian, and rap (rp.) in Romansh. ==Banknotes== * 10 francs * 20 francs * 50 francs * 100 francs * 200 francs * 1000 francs ==Coins== * 1 centime (not used commonly) * 2 centimes (not used commonly) * 5 centimes * 10 centimes * 20 centimes * Â½ franc * 1 franc * 2 francs * 5 francs ==Notes== ==Other websites== * Category:Currency of Europe Category:Economy of Switzerland Category:Liechtenstein
